"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## The public domain continues to roar back after decades in a coma.\\n\\n[![Cory Doctorow](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/0\\\\*ohRxgNPUyuFod_kY.jpeg)](https://doctorow.medium.com/?source=post_page-----2c4520dd2f3a-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://doctorow.medium.com/?source=post_page-----2c4520dd2f3a-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Cory Doctorow](https://doctorow.medium.com/?source=post_page-----2c4520dd2f3a-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://doctorow.medium.com/happy-public-domain-day-2c4520dd2f3a?source=post_page-----2c4520dd2f3a-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[2 days ago·6 min read](https://doctorow.medium.com/happy-public-domain-day-2c4520dd2f3a?source=post_page-----2c4520dd2f3a-----------------------------------)\\n\\n![The Duke Center for the Public Domain’s collage of artwork from movies, music and books that entered the public domain on Jan 1.](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*wNgmKO0\\\\_9IGBGYdTaM7Spg.jpeg)\\n\\nOn January 1, 2019 something extraordinary happened. For the first time since 1998, the American public domain got bigger.\\n\\nWhat happened in 1998? Congress — led by Rep Sonny Bono — extended the copyright on all works by 20 years. Works that had already been in the public domain went back…\\n\",\"timestamp\":1641433250,\"title\":\"Happy Public Domain Day! - Cory Doctorow - Medium\"},\"digest\":\"mRbsvDesnu_C69RtHUbIMfPronkmiFQuez9Pyf3mOZk\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xeae36B80859Af0F93d0621DCaD49eBCa43F02e3E\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"gwomdPjk-vAMDZY_MDrdoJOeKVrxSW3W2JtsDQVLn68\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"mHoJcOU-wf3wssFV3_bAFwvp-VbYnIdhN0Q309FNXzE\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"24aCYh3WEAuYvFZexWUyscBInIENPnL3tsIMxKGQs9ZTpApsczEEwYUxmCsg5lDKQmjZtjs3IeFkCV2eZGZXgg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xa627b5b8abd5ecb8bfbe243f9494eb8703294a02e91b87e2bf70c62dc6a4deb8